item.title: All-Inclusive Minneapolis Craft Brewery Tour
item.description: Learn about the Minneapolis brewpub scene and enjoy as many craft beer varieties as you like on this guided, all-you-can-drink, small-group brewery tour. Choose an afternoon or evening tour time, then visit local breweries that may include Fair State Brewing Co-op, Lakes and Legends Brewing Company, Modist Brewing or others. Snacks and round-trip transportation by minibus included.

image.alt: All-Inclusive Minneapolis Craft Brewery Tour

item.title: Twin Cities Highlights Tour
item.description: Get oriented with Minneapolis and St. Paul, aka the Twin Cities of Minnesota, on a highlights tour that introduces you to the area's major sights. You'll see modern and historical architecture and explore the neighborhoods between the two cities on this half-day tour. Enjoy the chance to sit back and relax instead of finding your own way around town.

image.alt: Twin Cities Highlights Tour

item.title: St. Paul Historic Cave Tour
item.description: Explore the only remaining restored Gangster Era site in Saint Paul on this guided historic caves tour of the Wabasha Street Caves. Carved into the hillside near downtown Saint Paul, the caves have been numerous things throughout their history, including as a gangster hot spot during Prohibition. Tour the caves and hear fascinating stories of their history from your guide.

image.alt: St. Paul Historic Cave Tour

item.title: Narrated Scenic Trolley Tour in Minneapolis, Minnesota
item.description: This tour is a one-of-a-kind trolley tour here in Minneapolis. There is no other Trolley in the city and this tour showcases a wide variety of locations that are historical, fun, culturally significant, and much more.

image.alt: Narrated Scenic Trolley Tour in Minneapolis, Minnesota

item.title: Candlelight Ghost Trolley Tour in Minneapolis
item.description:
Are you afraid of the dark? Join us for our Haunted Trolley Tour of Minneapolis! It is a spine-tingling journey to the most haunted sites in the City, aboard an historic trolley which itself is said to be haunted.
Your knowledgeable narrator will explain the legend and the lore surrounding the most paranormal happenings in our City's history.
Prepare for mysterious sightings, strange sounds, and shadows lurking around the corners. The tour begins and ends at a real Haunted Historic Mansion, 300 Clifton in Minneapolis.

image.alt: Candlelight Ghost Trolley Tour in Minneapolis

item.title: Twin City Ghosts Tour By US Ghost Adventures
item.description: Take a chilling ghost tour along Summit Avenue, Minneapolis, when you book this nighttime tour. Uncover the haunted history of mansions and historic locations, including Forepaugh's 2nd Mansion and Cochran Park, in Minneapolis-Saint Paul. This walking tour offers spine-tingling tales, snacks, and a lantern-lit journey through the supernatural side of Summit Avenue.

image.alt: Twin City Ghosts Tour By US Ghost Adventures

item.title: Complete Minneapolis Walking Tour
item.description: Learn all about the past and present of Minnesota and Minneapolis from a tour guide to help you see the best of the city. Spend three hours on a walking tour led by an enthusiastic, friendly guide who’s excited to share what they know about Minneapolis with you, from the Skyway System footbridges to artisan coffee roasters, soon you’ll know the city like a local.

image.alt: Complete Minneapolis Walking Tour

item.title: 15-Mile Aerial Helicopter Tour over Duluth and Superior
item.description: Get unobstructed views of landmarks in Duluth and around Lake Superior on a 15-minute scenic helicopter flight in Minnesota. Glide over Lake Superior and the shoreline as your pilot points out places such as Enger Tower and Aerial Lift Bridge. Hear live commentary through the provided headset as you take in the sights from the helicopter.

image.alt: 15-Mile Aerial Helicopter Tour over Duluth and Superior

item.title: SEA LIFE Aquarium Minnesota Admission Ticket at Mall of America
item.description: Discover marine life wonders at SEA LIFE Minnesota, an aquarium boasting more than 10,000 sea creatures. Located in the Mall of America, SEA LIFE provides the perfect break from shopping and change of scenery. Explore four themed tanks including Amazon River, Atlantis, Sturgeon Lake and Rainbow Reef. Check out the Octopus Garden, gaze eyes on the world’s largest crab species, and walk through an underwater tunnel and see the underbellies of stingrays and turtles.

image.alt: SEA LIFE Aquarium Minnesota Admission Ticket at Mall of America

item.title: The Escape Game: Epic 60-Minute Adventures at the Mall of America
item.description: Have a fun and exciting time trying to get your way out of an escape room in the Mall of America in Minneapolis. You and your party will have to solve clues and follow clues in order to get out in time. There are five games to choose from, like Gold Rush or Prison Break, so you decide. Then use your communication and teamwork skills to complete a mission.

image.alt: The Escape Game: Epic 60-Minute Adventures at the Mall of America

item.title: Minneapolis River Walk: A Self-Guided Audio Tour
item.description: This isn’t your grandma’s walking tour. With this self-paced audio guide, you’ll learn all about Minneapolis’s standard history (like Prince) *and* discover its secret nooks and crannies, like the history of “Funkytown,” a mansion with 86 TVs, and the invention of Zubaz pants. No matter what, after you’ve explored with this River Walk guide, you’ll never look at this stretch of the Mississippi with glazed-over eyes again.

image.alt: Minneapolis River Walk: A Self-Guided Audio Tour

item.title: Minneapolis & St. Paul Highlights Private Riding & Walking Tour (3 hrs)
item.description: See the best of the Twin Cities on foot and from a private car on this guided tour of Minneapolis and St. Paul. This sixteen-stop tour covers the best of both cities. See where the professional sports teams play at Xcel Energy Center and Target Field. Pass by some of the area’s serene spaces like Lake of the Isles and Minnehaha Falls. Visit the Minnesota State Capitol and Mill District while listening to local stories.

image.alt: Minneapolis & St. Paul Highlights Private Riding & Walking Tour (3 hrs)

item.title: Saint Paul Gangster Tour
item.description: Saint Paul is the current capital of Minnesota and was quite the hub for organized crime not too long ago. Discover this thrilling part of the Twin Cities history during a gangster tour by bus. You’ll join a group of history buffs for a ride through the city, spending hours learning about the 1930s Prohibition Era from your funny and informative guide. Venture through South, West, and Central Saint Paul, stopping at sites of payroll robberies, bars where gangsters frequented, and spots where kidnappings took place.

image.alt: Saint Paul Gangster Tour

item.title: The Complete St. Paul Walking Tour
item.description: Minneapolis gets a lot of attention, but this tour gets you a proper introduction to the other half of the Twin Cities: Saint Paul. The capital city of Minnesota has a history full of intriguing stories like tales of the illegal alcohol production during Prohibition. You’ll join a guide for a walk around Saint Paul, through both quiet neighborhoods and bustling downtown as you learn about the city’s secrets; including the secret caves that are closer than you’d believe.

image.alt: The Complete St. Paul Walking Tour

item.title: Minneapolis Skyway Walking Tour
item.description:
A great tour year-round, especially if you're visiting in the winter months! Minneapolis is home to the largest, contiguous skyway system in the world! Originally designed to counter the 1950s post war suburban boom by revitalizing the city's retail core, today the second story walkways connect 80 city blocks and meander more than 9 miles. This is a great way to see the city - inside and out - during cool weather, hot weather, rainy days and the brutally long Minnesota winter, so pretty much year-round! There are so many treasures within downtown's unique architectural landscape, and the skyway system is sometimes the only way to see them. The skyway is such a huge part of our city's identity, the Replacements even wrote a song about it, aptly named Skyway.
Choosing Mpls City & Skyway Tours, you are supporting a local, woman-owned small business with a big heart.
(Please note, this is a walking tour. We will walk up to two miles, with breaks. Wear comfortable shoes and bring water.)

image.alt: Minneapolis Skyway Walking Tour

item.title: 30-Mile North Shore Helicopter Tour
item.description: See Duluth, Minnesota, from the air during a small-group helicopter tour that travels 30 miles (48 kilometers) along the north shore of Lake Superior. Settle into your comfortable window seat and enjoy spectacular birds-eye views as you fly over the Port Terminal, aerial lift bridge, and Canal Park waterways, and along the north shore, taking in views of the Glensheen Mansion, Hawks Ridge, and the Lester River.

image.alt: 30-Mile North Shore Helicopter Tour

item.title: In the Footsteps of Prince: A Self-Guided Audio Tour of Downtown Minneapolis
item.description: Explore Minneapolis through Prince’s life—without dealing with any of the crowds. On this self-guided audio tour, you’ll hit the streets of Prince’s favorite 'hood, starting at Nicollet Avenue and ending on First Avenue, where 10,000 gathered to mourn the artist’s death. Though designed for a 75-minute tour, explore at your pace, sinking into all things purple.

image.alt: In the Footsteps of Prince: A Self-Guided Audio Tour of Downtown Minneapolis

item.title: Twin Cities Walking Tour: Uncover Hidden Minneapolis Bars
item.description: If you’ve got a thirst for knowledge, exploration, and a good time in a new place, this historical walking tour of Minneapolis’s bars is a great activity for you. Stroll through one half of the Twin Cities on a bar-hopping tour. You’ll do more than sample the beer and cocktails offered by friendly bartenders; you’ll learn the history of each of the four bars you visit.

image.alt: Twin Cities Walking Tour: Uncover Hidden Minneapolis Bars

item.title: Minneapolis Afternoon Snack
item.description: Starting in the trendy North Loop neighborhood, we visit some of the best restaurants in Minneapolis! Learn about the city over a bite to eat (or four)! From the best ranked pizza joint in the country, to classic upper midwest cuisine, and a little bit from northeast Minneapolis' eastern European heritage, this tour will leave both your brain and belly full! And don't forget to leave room for dessert!

image.alt: Minneapolis Afternoon Snack

item.title: Minnehaha Falls: A Self-Guided Audio Tour of Minneapolis
item.description: One of the greatest urban waterfalls in the nation, this self-guided audio tour turns Minnehaha Falls into a world of fascination and wonder. Using just your smartphone, you’ll follow along as you learn stories of hermits and Presidents, nature and geology, and much more. Speed through your experience or linger as you like, turning it into a discovery of your own making.

image.alt: Minnehaha Falls: A Self-Guided Audio Tour of Minneapolis

item.title: Minneapolis Indoor Skydiving Admission with 2 Flights & Personalized Certificate
item.description: Take a break from sightseeing in Minneapolis to experience the rush of skydiving—without jumping from an airplane. Those afraid of heights will love this activity, which includes two “jumps” and takes place inside of a high-velocity wind tunnel with an instructor at your side. No experience is necessary and participants of all skill levels can join in.

image.alt: Minneapolis Indoor Skydiving Admission with 2 Flights & Personalized Certificate

item.title: Self-Guided Audio Tour Lake Superior North Shore
item.description:
Download the GuideAlong self-guided audio tour and you'll discover more on your Lake Superior North Shore road trip. Hear fascinating behind-the-scenes stories, local tips and directions play automatically along Highway 61, all based on your location.
You'll be guided to all of the area's famous highlights as well as lessor known gems including one of Minnesota's most photographed lighthouses, a historic mansion that's also the site of a famous murder mystery, and an iconic 932-foot-high scenic lookout over Lake Superior.
Enjoy the freedom to explore offline at your own pace, spending more time at places that interest you, and bypass any that don’t.
- Stories, tips and directions play automatically based on your location - Travel at your own pace - Tour offline using GPS, no cell service or WiFi needed - Suggested itineraries for half, full or multi day use - No time limits or expiry, free updates - Like having a tour guide along for the drive
Purchase one tour per vehicle.

image.alt: Self-Guided Audio Tour Lake Superior North Shore

item.title: Walking St. Paul Summit Ave. Victorian Homes Private Tour (2 hrs)
item.description: Summit Avenue in St. Paul, Minnesota is home to some of the state’s most beautiful Victorian architecture. Embark on a private tour and learn about these preserved structures from your guide. Listen to stories of wealthy families and tycoons who lives more than 120 years ago and built these charming estates. Architecture lovers can spot several styles including Queen Anne, neo-classical, Romanesque, and Georgian Revival during the tour.

image.alt: Walking St. Paul Summit Ave. Victorian Homes Private Tour (2 hrs)

item.title: Minneapolis Past and Present
item.description: Walk with local guides through Minneapolis! Learn the surprising and often untold history of Minneapolis and the state it's in, from before statehood and through to the present

image.alt: Minneapolis Past and Present
